    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error as defined in ASME V&V 40 Section 4.3.4 pertains to iterative solver convergence tolerance effects in nonlinear or time-dependent analyses where residual accumulation can bias QoI predictions. The pedicle screw compression-bending model employs a direct sparse solver (Ansys Sparse Direct) for the linear static load steps; no iterative convergence loop is present and therefore no iterative solver error can accumulate. The nonlinear contact iterations use tight force and displacement convergence criteria (1e-4 relative norm) verified to produce residuals below floating-point round-off for this problem size. Accordingly, this factor does not apply to the present analysis context."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-use-error",
