        "description": "Linear elastic isotropic material model justified by stress-strain characterization showing elastic behavior up to yield for Ti-6Al-4V ELI at the strain rates imposed. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) validated against published tribology data for titanium-on-UHMWPE. Model form assumptions documented and supported by literature references."
      },
      "rationale": "The choice of linear elastic material model for the titanium screw and rod is justified by the operating stress range remaining below 80% of yield strength for the primary QoI evaluation window. Geometric nonlinearity (large displacement) is included for the 40 mm displacement QoI. Achieved level 3 (model form assumptions formally justified by supporting data) meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
