        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Material properties (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34, Sy=880 MPa for Ti-6Al-4V ELI) sourced from ASTM F136 and lot-specific coupon testing. Geometric dimensions derived from manufacturer CAD files with tolerances documented. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo propagation (500 samples); 95th-percentile QoI variation < 4%."
      },
      "rationale": "All material and geometric inputs are traceable to primary sources. Uncertainty propagation performed via Monte Carlo with 500 LHS samples. Input sensitivity ranked; elastic modulus and screw diameter are dominant contributors. Required level 3 (formal uncertainty propagation) achieved."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-test-samples",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria",
        "description": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes). Samples drawn from production lots; dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to engineering drawings within ±0.05 mm. Inter-laboratory variability < 5% CV for stiffness."
      },
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs across two laboratories provide adequate statistical power for comparison against FEA ensemble predictions. Dimensional inspection records on file. Inter-laboratory reproducibility confirmed. Achieved level 3 (multi-laboratory, production-representative samples with dimensional verification) exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized test configuration (10-degree offset compression-bending). Only this single loading condition was evaluated. Required level 3 would demand multiple loading angles or rates; achieved level 2 reflects single standardized condition with full environmental control documentation."
      },
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 mandates a single 10-degree compression-bending configuration. The validation study faithfully replicates this condition with calibrated load frames (NIST-traceable calibration certificates on file) and controlled displacement rate (5 mm/min). However, only this single test condition was evaluated; no parametric variation of loading angle or rate was performed. This limits the factor to achieved level 2 against a required level 3. The shortfall is addressed in the offset rationale within the decision record."
    },
    {
